Usage: merge_model_timing [-help] [-keep_separate_arc] -library_file <string>
                          -mode_group <string> -modes <string>
                          [-outfile <string>] [-pin_cap_tolerance <float>]
                          [-tolerance <float>]

-help                            # Prints out the command usage
-keep_separate_arc               # always create a separate timing arcs with
                                 # respective mode been appended. (bool, optional)
-library_file <string>           # Input Library files that needs to be merged
                                 # (string, required)
-mode_group <string>             # Mode group name (string, required)
-modes <string>                  # Mode names required for merging the
                                 # libraries. The number of mode names should
                                 # be equal to the number of input libraries
                                 # (string, required)
-outfile <string>                # The final Merged Library Output file name.
                                 # (string, optional)
-pin_cap_tolerance <float>       # pin capacitance tolerance  for making
                                 # tolerance comparsion for library merging.
                                 # (float, optional)
-tolerance <float>               # tolerance value for making tolerance
                                 # comparsion for library merging.
                                 # (float, optional)